theorem Topology.interior_preimage_subset_preimage_closure
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]
    {f : X → Y} (hf : Continuous f) {B : Set Y} :
    interior (f ⁻¹' B) ⊆ f ⁻¹' closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, view the point as lying in the closure of the preimage.
  have hxCl : (x : X) ∈ closure (f ⁻¹' B) := subset_closure hx
  -- Next, apply the previously proved inclusion for closures of preimages.
  have hIncl :=
    Topology.continuous_closure_preimage_subset
      (X := X) (Y := Y) (f := f) hf (B := B)
  exact hIncl hxCl
